column3: Changes in reserves has been excluded as these relate to gold loans, and do not accurately reflect the level of RBA gold reserves. Please see: https://www.rba.gov.au/qa/gold-holding.html and https://www.rba.gov.au/publications/bulletin/2017/dec/1.html
Purchase of 10 tonnes from the IMF took place in September 2010

The purchase of 454 tonnes of gold, announced in April 2009 took place over a six-year period from 2003 - 2009. The purchase of 604 tonnes of gold, announced in June 2016 took place over a six-year period from 2009 - 2016.
Transfer to ECB on joining Eurozone (Gold is 15% of contribution to ECB reserves), Janauary 2008
Transfer of gold in May 2014 part of entering into a three-year swap agreement. Gold to be returned when swap agreement terminates.
The purchase of 200 tonnes from the IMF took place in November 2009
Transfer to ECB on joining Eurozone (Gold is 15% of contribution to ECB reserves), January 2014
Transfer to ECB on joining Eurozone (Gold is 15% of contribution to ECB reserves), January 2008. Sales under CBGA 2 and 3.
The purchase of 2 tonnes from the IMF took place in November 2009
Buys locally produced gold; may sell or retain in reserves
Mainly purchases of gold in the domestic market & other changes
SAMA announced in June that gold data from Q1 2008 has been modified, due to an adjustment of SAMAs gold accounts.
Transfer to ECB on joining Eurozone (Gold is 15% of contribution to ECB reserves), January 2009. Sales under CBGA 3.
Transfer to ECB on joining Eurozone (Gold is 15% of contribution to ECB reserves), January 2007
Repayment of gold loan June 2003; previously adjustments to gold holdings held under loan which was dollar denominated.

Gold has been added to Turkeys balance sheet as a result of the policy accepting gold in its reserve requirements from commercial banks. Please see this link for information on this policy action http://www.tcmb.gov.tr/wps/wcm/connect/57c5777d-1f48-4eb4-98ba-af4c6aaddc20/ANO2012-38.pdf?MOD=AJPERES&CACHEID=57c5777d-1f48-4eb4-98ba-af4c6aaddc20

Since May 2017 Turkeys central bank has been increasing its gold reserves by purchasing gold outright. We therefore decided to publish the figure for Turkeys official gold reserves exclusive of ROM holdings, to better reflect true central bank holdings. Please see this link for information on this policy action http://www.tcmb.gov.tr/wps/wcm/connect/57c5777d-1f48-4eb4-98ba-af4c6aaddc20/ANO2012-38.pdf?MOD=AJPERES&CACHEID=57c5777d-1f48-4eb4-98ba-af4c6aaddc20
